text: Magadi is an impact crater in the Argyre quadrangle of Mars, located at 34.5°S and 46.1°W. It is 51 km in diameter. Its name refers to Magadi, a town in Kenya. ==See also== * List of craters on Mars: H-N == References == Category:Argyre quadrangle Category:Impact craters on Mars
title: Magadi (crater)
